 changed to how they already are as you stated.<br>
<br>
Solo my epic is 70% if not more of my damage. I hardly ever nuke solo. I use boot nukes and after 6 to 7 mobs just reclaim and remake epic. Makes for zero downtime and fast killing. I would be happy to see mage pets doing 70% total damage and the mage doing 30%. What that does is, it gives us more for room to argue to stay on top of the pet food chain which is where I want to be. I made a mage because we are the best pet class that can nuke. The current problem is the pets are really not much better then necro pets while our nuking is below druid standards.  I think our nukes in PoP could use some tweaks and fixes for sure but I think if the pets make up for the sad nuke display i can maybe swallow some of the crappy nukes.<br>
<br>
I think the biggest problem is not pet vs. the mage's offense. The problem is pet vs. mage defense. To much of our defense is tied into the pet. 95% pet/ 5% mage looks to be about right. The problem is the pet is a offensive tool while being our only defensive tool. When our defense dies so does near 50% of our offense. What compounds the problem is when the pet dies his offense is now gone but ALSO so is the mage's offense. The pet defends us, while doing 40% of our offensive damage. The pet also allows the mage to do damage. Once the pet dies the ability of the mage to do damage is gone completely.  No other class has this problem in the game. I think this is in need of a fix much more so then mage damage vs. pet damage.<br>
<br>
