<br>
If I wanted most of my damage to be in nukes, I would have created a Wizard.  In my opinion, nukes are wizard territory.  They should be the undisputed kings of nuking, which it think (and hope) everyone agrees with here.  However, if nuking was the primary source of Mage damage, then that wouldn't really make us much different than wizards then, now would it?  <br>
<br>
Mages and Wizards are quite similiar; their jobs are to do damage.  However, they achieve this in quite a different manner.  Being a mage, I want my damage to be done through a pet.  Why?  Cause that's how I envision a Magician.  Nukes, although very important, are more-so secondary to me.<br>
<br>
